    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our lineup leans heavily into aggressive base-running and high-ceiling park factors. **Mickey Moniak** leads the charge with an elite 75.98 efficiency score; he benefits from a highly favorable matchup against Holmes and a massive 14% boost from park factors and platoon splits, making him our must-start anchor. Similarly, **Austin Riley** checks in at 73.69, taking full advantage of a juicy matchup against Quintana (5.47 xERA) and a park environment that sky-rockets his power projection. We are also prioritizing stolen base upside with **Brice Turang** (72.12) and **Jose Caballero** (69.65). Despite facing an elite hold rate from the opposing battery, **Jose Caballero** earns a strong recommendation due to his dynamic platoon advantage against the lefty Povich, while **Brice Turang**\u2019s placement in the two-hole provides the optimal runway to capitalize on his speed.\n\nThe decision to bench **Josh Naylor** (43.14) was the most difficult call of the morning. While his raw base projection remains solid, the matchup against Ragans\u2014an elite arm with a 3.07 xERA\u2014crushed his efficiency score, pushing him below the threshold required to displace our starters in more favorable hitting environments. We must keep a close eye on the weather, as the wind-in factor is dampening the outlook for **Gabriel Moreno**, **Corbin Carroll**, and **Seiya Suzuki**. While **Corbin Carroll** remains a core start due to his 71.61 efficiency and game-breaking speed, the -5% wind adjustment limits his ceiling. Meanwhile, **James Wood** is in a \"prove-it\" spot; despite a high 10% boost for his leadoff position, he faces a challenging arm in Misiorowski, requiring a disciplined approach to justify his start over our secondary bench depth.",
